# UI/UX Standards

## Design System

- Use **Tailwind CSS v4** for all styling
- Follow mobile-first responsive design principles
- Implement consistent spacing using Tailwind's spacing scale
- Use semantic color tokens for theming

## Component Guidelines

- Create reusable, composable components
- Implement proper loading states and skeleton screens
- Use consistent error handling with user-friendly messages
- Implement proper focus management and keyboard navigation
- Use ARIA labels and roles for accessibility

## Layout & Navigation

- Implement responsive navigation that works on all devices
- Use consistent page layouts with proper header/footer
- Implement breadcrumbs for complex navigation flows
- Ensure proper visual hierarchy with typography and spacing

## Forms & Inputs

- Use Zod for form validation with real-time feedback
- Implement proper error states and success confirmations
- Use appropriate input types (email, password, URL, etc.)
- Implement proper form accessibility with labels and descriptions
- Show loading states during form submission

## Data Display

- Use appropriate data visualization for analytics (charts, tables, cards)
- Implement proper empty states for no data scenarios
- Use pagination for large datasets
- Implement search and filtering where appropriate
- Show loading skeletons while data loads

## QR Code Specific UI

- Display QR codes prominently with download options
- Show QR code metadata clearly (name, slug, target URL)
- Implement version history with clear timestamps
- Provide easy editing interface for target URLs
- Show scan analytics in an intuitive dashboard format

## Accessibility Requirements

- Ensure proper color contrast ratios
- Implement keyboard navigation for all interactive elements
- Use semantic HTML elements
- Provide alternative text for images and icons
- Test with screen readers and keyboard-only navigation
